# BROWSER-core.md - PH Global Rules

All evaluate/snapshot calls MUST include `profile: "{{browser_profile}}"`.

**Global rules:**
- `evaluate()` for data extraction, text input, state checks
- `snapshot()` ONLY before clicks. CLI flags are booleans — NO values:
  ```
  opentwins browser snapshot --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} --selector "..." --compact --interactive --depth 6 --json
  ```
  ❌ `--compact true` / `--interactive true` — these fail ("too many arguments")
  ✅ `--compact --interactive` — correct boolean flag syntax
- Wait 3s before first snapshot on any page
- NEVER use `args` in evaluate — inline via template literals
- PH editor = TipTap/ProseMirror (`.tiptap.ProseMirror`). NEVER set `textContent`/`innerHTML`/`value` — use `execCommand('insertText')`
- `click` takes ref as **positional argument**, not an option:
  ```
  opentwins browser click --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} e1 --json
  ```
  ❌ `click --ref e1` — fails ("unknown option --ref")
  ✅ `click e1` — correct positional argument
- ❌ NEVER use `browser.act({ kind: "navigate" })` — "navigate" is NOT a valid kind. Use `opentwins browser open "URL"` via exec
- ❌ NEVER use separate `exec sleep N` for page load waits — combine waits into the NEXT evaluate call using a leading `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));` or simply accept that the evaluate will run immediately (PH pages load fast)
- `evaluate --fn` takes **inline code**, not a file path. Pass the function body directly:
  ```
  opentwins browser evaluate --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} --fn 'function(){return document.title;}' --json
  ```
  ❌ `--fn /tmp/script.js` — fails (reads literal string, not file)
  ❌ heredoc piped to `--fn` — fails ("Invalid regular expression flags")
  ✅ `--fn 'function(){...}'` — correct inline syntax
- `open` for navigation, NOT `navigate`:
  ```
  opentwins browser open --browser-profile {{browser_profile}} "https://example.com" --json
  ```
  ❌ `navigate --url "..."` — fails ("missing required argument 'url'")
  ✅ `open "URL"` — correct positional argument

## Recovery Rules

- Browser timeout → close tab, reopen URL. If fails → `exec opentwins browser start --profile {{browser_profile}}`, wait 3s, retry once. NEVER use `browser.stop()`.
- "matched N elements" error → snapshot selector too broad, use narrower selector
- evaluate() unexpected data → 1 snapshot to inspect DOM, use discovered selector
- Click fails after snapshot → retry snapshot with narrower selector, retry click
- Retry also fails → skip, log Error, move to next task
